review_title: Come for the surf, stay for the pool and view
review_text_liked: From previous reviews, I was not sure what to expect, but this is an absolute gem. The pool and view are the standout features and it was nice that there was enough seating. We had one of the cheaper rooms with AC and it was perfectly fine. It was a large room with comfortable bed, fridge, working AC and plenty of hot water. It had a typical bathroom where everything gets wet: a little annoying to begin with but you get used to it. Each of the cheaper bungalows were separate from each other with brick walls, so you have no problems with noisy neighbours. It looked like the more expensive rooms were in 2 storey buildings at the back. Breakfast was ordered from a menu and freshly made. The included breakfast was one choice from the usual breakfast fare, one drink and a plate of fruit. It was very nice. It would be nice if there was a little more furniture like bedside tables and something to put your bags on rather than the floor. Lights by the bed for reading would be nice. New towels and bed linen would improve things however these are all quite trivial. Overall this is a great place and I would love to come back.

The rooms are simple with no frills ( however had reliable air con) but spacious and the bed was comfortable
review_text_disliked: Thereâ€™s nothing to not like - the location and the laid-back feel are winners. Itâ€™s budget-style so donâ€™t expect fancy rooms. The wifi can be a bit unreliable and the power went off at least once during my 5-night stay but these were small inconveniences. NOTE - my friends and I both had a little trouble getting a ride-share back down to Kuta once we checked out. Availability is sparse. You might want to do a little forward planning by organising a driver in advance if you are on a tight timeline (I wasnâ€™t, so it wasnâ€™t a huge issue for me).

review_title: Excellent as always. We love The Gubug and love visiting Balian
review_text_liked: Gubug is a budget friendly surfer accomodation at Balian Beach and is situated in a great location from the beach and other restaurants and food outlets. It offers a simple clean bedroom and bathroom villa close to everything in Balian. If you want to go exploring in the highlands the friendly staff can arrange either rental scooters or a car and driver. Watch out for the traffic on the main Gillimaluk Road as it can be very busy and dangerous.
review_text_disliked: The Beds in the Villas rooms are not amazingly comfortable but this is not a resort style accomodation and you can always go down the road a bit (or up) and pay twice the price for fancier accomodation

review_title: GREAT SURFIE LOCATION, ROOM NOT UP TO PAR
review_text_liked: Nice big pool, clean, warmed by the sun, nice to have lawn and trees, flowering staghorn plants. Room had aircon and a fridge. Staff pleasant. Location close to the beach, great little Deki's Warung across the road had good cheap food and drinks and you could watch the surf and sunsets from there, good hangout for surfers. Could refill water bottles from breakfast bar. Staff happy to arrange transport. Good location for getting away from tourist bustle and shopping, but you could walk 20+ mins to the main road to local shops and ATMs. Good massage salon Ayu Bagus 5 min walk. Appreciated the drying rack. Close enough to walk on the black-sand beach, (even though there was a fair amount of rubbish on it).
review_text_disliked: Unfortunately, Room 1 was not good, especially the bathroom . Apart from the poor state of fixtures and fittings and bad staining on tiles, and although the shower was hot and decent pressure, the positioning meant you had to stand awkwardly in a corner, and the toilet was also showered. I asked to see a Superior Room and it was tidier but the layout of all bathrooms the same, I was told. Also the room was dark, even during the day with the lights on, not enough light to read by. No bedside table, lamp. Curtains torn and hanging off. Attention seems to be paid to the grounds but it seems not to this room. I would not stay here again.
